body:
**Describe the bug**

When your `hardhat.config.js` definition for an Optimistic Ethereum network does not contain a `gasPrice` value, you get this error:

```
     Error: failed to get consistent fee data (operation="signer.getFeeData", code=UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION, version=abstract-signer/5.4.0)
      at Logger.makeError (node_modules/@ethersproject/logger/src.ts/index.ts:213:28)
      at Logger.throwError (node_modules/@ethersproject/logger/src.ts/index.ts:225:20)
      at Wallet.<anonymous> (node_modules/@ethersproject/abstract-signer/src.ts/index.ts:278:28)
      at step (node_modules/@ethersproject/abstract-signer/lib/index.js:48:23)
      at Object.next (node_modules/@ethersproject/abstract-signer/lib/index.js:29:53)
      at fulfilled (node_modules/@ethersproject/abstract-signer/lib/index.js:20:58)
      at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:97:5)
 ```

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Run an Optimistic Ethereum server through `docker-compose up`.
2. Create a hardhat sample project.
3. Edit `hardhat.config.js` to add the network:
```
    optimistic: {
       url: 'http://127.0.0.1:8545',
       accounts: {
         mnemonic: 'test test test test test test test test test test test junk'
       },
       // This sets the gas price to 0 for all transactions on L2. We do this
       // because account balances are not automatically initiated with an ETH
       // balance (yet, sorry!).
       // gasPrice: 15000000,
       ovm: true // This sets the network as using the ovm and ensure contract will be compiled against that.
    }
```
4. Run `npx hardhat test --network optimistic`

**Solution**

Add a `gasPrice` value, either 0 or 15000000:

````
    optimistic: {
       url: 'http://127.0.0.1:8545',
       accounts: {
         mnemonic: 'test test test test test test test test test test test junk'
       },
       // This sets the gas price to 0 for all transactions on L2. We do this
       // because account balances are not automatically initiated with an ETH
       // balance (yet, sorry!).
       gasPrice: 15000000,
       ovm: true // This sets the network as using the ovm and ensure contract will be compiled against that.
    }
```
